Interactive Data Visualization for Global Health

Lecture 6: (Geographic) Maps

Geographic maps provide a very engaging visual element, and can contextualize our work in global health.

Comparisons between geographically close areas can provide insight as well as motivation.

Borrowing strength from geographically near areas is also a method we often use to fill in the gaps in our sparse and noisy data. But that is a story for another time.

Today, we will have a look at how to include maps in IDVs with D3js.

And, we will continue our example-based d3 drills, and try to push forwards our projects.

Outline:

  • results of peer critiques,
  • javascript quiz/exercise,
  • geographic maps and data,
  • getting data in to Javascript,
  • geographic maps in d3,
  • project work time.
